Ministerial Briefing Session: Progress Report on the re opening of schools and measures to curb the spread of Covid- 19 in schools (Minister of Basic Education and MECs for Education) JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is expected to provide more clarity on the next phase of school reopening during a briefing on Thursday. Motshekga published the directives on Wednesday. She says the department will work to ensure everything is ready for pupils to return from next month. READ: Next phase of schools reopening to take place next month On 6 July, several grades are due back in class. They include Grade R, 1, 2 ,3 , 6 and 11. This comes as COVID-19 cases continue to surge in the country. Motshekga is expected to provide more clarity during a briefing on Thursday.